BLOCK 3 — Add columns 5-8
        (Effective From · Effective To · Changed By · Change Reason)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

WHERE: Still in the column editor for pei_ruleversion.
       Click "+ New column" for each below, one at a time.


─── COLUMN 5: Effective From ────────────────────────────────────

Display name:        Effective From
Schema name:         pei_effectivefrom
                     (verify — should read pei_effectivefrom)
Data type:           Date and time
                     (NOT "Date only" — we need time component)
Format:              Date and time
Behavior:            User local
                     (★ Advanced options → Behavior — important;
                      "Date only" or "Time-zone independent" are
                      WRONG. Behavior is set ONCE at create and
                      cannot be changed later.)
Column requirement:  Business required
Searchable:          Yes

Click Save.


─── COLUMN 6: Effective To ──────────────────────────────────────

Display name:        Effective To
Schema name:         pei_effectiveto
Data type:           Date and time
Format:              Date and time
Behavior:            User local
Column requirement:  Optional
                     (★ NOT Required — null = currently-effective
                      version; this is spec-required behavior)
Searchable:          Yes

Click Save.


─── COLUMN 7: Changed By ────────────────────────────────────────

Display name:        Changed By
Schema name:         pei_changedby
                     (verify — pei_changedby, not pei_changed_by)
Data type:           Lookup
Related table:       User (systemuser)
                     ← search the dropdown for "User" — the table
                       you want is the system User table (the one
                       Dataverse calls SystemUser internally).
                       NOT "Owner", NOT "Team", NOT a custom user
                       table.
Column requirement:  Business required
Searchable:          Yes

  ★ When you Save and get the relationship-behavior dialog
    (like Column 1):

       Type of behavior:  Referential
       Delete:            Remove Link

    (Leave defaults — DO NOT set Restrict here. Spec doesn't
     ask for restrict on Changed By; we don't want to block
     SystemUser deletes/disables on account of audit-trail
     references. Referential / Remove Link is correct.)

  Click Done.


─── COLUMN 8: Change Reason ─────────────────────────────────────

Display name:        Change Reason
Schema name:         pei_changereason
Data type:           Multiple lines of text
Format:              Text (Plain)
Maximum character count:  2000
Column requirement:  Optional
                     (★ NOT Required — human-authored note,
                      may be blank)
Searchable:          Yes

Click Save.


